body: 👋 Hello @corehalt, thank you for your interest in YOLOv3 🚀! Please visit our ⭐️ [Tutorials](https://github.com/ultralytics/yolov3/wiki#tutorials) to get started, where you can find quickstart guides for simple tasks like [Custom Data Training](https://github.com/ultralytics/yolov3/wiki/Train-Custom-Data) all the way to advanced concepts like [Hyperparameter Evolution](https://github.com/ultralytics/yolov5/issues/607). If this is a 🐛 Bug Report, please provide screenshots and **minimum viable code to reproduce your issue**, otherwise we can not help you. If this is a custom training ❓ Question, please provide as much information as possible, including dataset images, training logs, screenshots, and a public link to online [W&B logging](https://github.com/ultralytics/yolov3/wiki/Train-Custom-Data#visualize) if available. For business inquiries or professional support requests please visit https://ultralytics.com or email Glenn Jocher at glenn.jocher@ultralytics.com. ## Requirements [**Python>=3.6.0**](https://www.python.org/) with all [requirements.txt](https://github.com/ultralytics/yolov3/blob/master/requirements.txt) installed including [**PyTorch>=1.7**](https://pytorch.org/get-started/locally/). To get started: ```bash $ git clone https://github.com/ultralytics/yolov3 $ cd yolov3 $ pip install -r requirements.txt ``` ## Environments YOLOv3 may be run in any of the following up-to-date verified environments (with all dependencies including [CUDA](https://developer.nvidia.com/cuda)/[CUDNN](https://developer.nvidia.com/cudnn), [Python](https://www.python.org/) and [PyTorch](https://pytorch.org/) preinstalled): - **Google Colab and Kaggle** notebooks with free GPU: - **Google Cloud** Deep Learning VM. See [GCP Quickstart Guide](https://github.com/ultralytics/yolov3/wiki/GCP-Quickstart) - **Amazon** Deep Learning AMI. See [AWS Quickstart Guide](https://github.com/ultralytics/yolov3/wiki/AWS-Quickstart) - **Docker Image**. See [Docker Quickstart Guide](https://github.com/ultralytics/yolov3/wiki/Docker-Quickstart) ## Status If this badge is green, all [YOLOv3 GitHub Actions](https://github.com/ultralytics/yolov3/actions) Continuous Integration (CI) tests are currently passing. CI tests verify correct operation of YOLOv3 training ([train.py](https://github.com/ultralytics/yolov3/blob/master/train.py)), validation ([val.py](https://github.com/ultralytics/yolov3/blob/master/val.py)), inference ([detect.py](https://github.com/ultralytics/yolov3/blob/master/detect.py)) and export ([export.py](https://github.com/ultralytics/yolov3/blob/master/export.py)) on MacOS, Windows, and Ubuntu every 24 hours and on every commit.

@corehalt yes I'm able to reproduce the same. Not sure what the issue might be. You could try exporting via the YOLOv5 repo, which is more up to date, though the repo doesn't seem to be the problem since YOLOv3-SPP exports correctly.
@corehalt unfortunately our support levels for the YOLOv3 repo are minimal as we support and grow YOLOv5, so I'll put a TODO on this, but I can't give you an ETA for when it might be solved.
@glenn-jocher just for the record, same issue also happens for yolov3-tiny.pt.

@corehalt hmm interesting. We probably just need to retrain all the YOLOv3 models with the latest YOLOv5 master, i.e. just use the yolov3 yamls with the YOLOv5 repo and retrain, and then these should be exportable.

When we released these models TFLite export was not fully supported, and it's still not part of our CI checks (though it should be).

@corehalt all https://github.com/ultralytics/yolov3 models are now retrained but original issue is not resolved with these new models.

New models are attached as updated release assets at https://github.com/ultralytics/yolov3/releases/tag/v9.6.0

@glenn-jocher Thank you for retraining the models.
An update on this is that even using the new yolov3 retrained model under `yolov5` repository I'm still getting the same issue:
```
TensorFlow Lite: export failure: 'NoneType' object has no attribute 'call'
```
@corehalt yeah sorry. Can you try debugging by removing the TFLite export `try: except` and tracing the source of the error?

@glenn-jocher I think I found the issue, now I can export correctly using `yolov3.yaml`
Seems that here https://github.com/ultralytics/yolov3/blob/master/models/yolov3.yaml#L31 there is a typo:
```
# YOLOv3 head
head:
  [[-1, 1, Bottleneck, [1024, False]],
   [-1, 1, Conv, [512, [1, 1]]],   <-------
   [-1, 1, Conv, [1024, 3, 1]],
```
to be able to export later in TF it should be changed to:
```
# YOLOv3 head
head:
  [[-1, 1, Bottleneck, [1024, False]],
   [-1, 1, Conv, [512, 1, 1]],   <------ no brackets
   [-1, 1, Conv, [1024, 3, 1]],
```

The problem is that any training that starts from the pre-trained yolov3.pt model will have this issue.
Only a train from the scratch will allow to export later to TF.

Is it possible for you to retrain the model with the updated yaml?

Thank you

Ah, the typo also appears in the yaml file configuration of the YoloV5 repo:
https://github.com/ultralytics/yolov5/blob/master/models/hub/yolov3.yaml#L31
